Below are the IT technical specifications you requested so our teams stay in sync:

1. Core Platform & Infrastructure
   • Cloud: AWS (us-east-1) with auto-scaling groups across 3 AZs.
   • Application Stack: Node.js 18 LTS (Express) + React 18 front-end, backed by PostgreSQL 14 (RDS) and Redis 7 (Elasticache) for caching/queues.
   • CI/CD: GitHub Actions → AWS CodeBuild/CodeDeploy. Average build time 6–8 min.

2. Integration & APIs
   • RESTful JSON API; base URL  https://api.tritondefense.com/v1
   • Auth: OAuth 2.0 client-credentials flow (token lifetime 60 min, refreshable).
   • Rate Limit: 600 requests/min per client ID; burst up to 1 000.
   • Webhook support for event types  order.created, order.fulfilled, campaign.analytics.complete.

3. Data Model Highlights
   • User table keyed by UUID (v4).
   • Orders, Campaigns, and EngagementMetrics tables are partitioned monthly for performance.
   • All timestamps stored in UTC (ISO-8601).

4. Security & Compliance
   • Data encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3) and at rest (AWS KMS CMK, AES-256).
   • OWASP Top-10 automated scans in CI; Snyk for dependency vulns.
   • SOC 2 Type II controls in place; annual penetration tests last completed Jan 2025.

5. Performance Benchmarks (current prod load)
   • P95 API latency: 240 ms (GET), 310 ms (POST).
   • DB CPU utilisation: 55 % peak, 25 % avg.
   • Cache hit ratio: 87 %; aiming > 90 % after Q3 tuning.

6. Roll-Out Timeline
   • Staging environment ready for Marketing tests: Mon 27 May.
   • UAT window: 27 May – 4 Jun.
   • Production cut-over scheduled for Tue 11 Jun @ 22:00 ET (≈ 30 min expected downtime).

